# ============================================
# Dexto - Crypto Mining Investment Platform
# Environment Variables Template
# ============================================

# Database (MongoDB Atlas - FREE tier recommended for Vercel)
# Get your free MongoDB Atlas connection string from: https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
# Format: mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@<cluster>.mongodb.net/<dbname>?retryWrites=true&w=majority
DATABASE_URL="mongodb+srv://dexto_admin:YOUR_PASSWORD_HERE@cluster0.abc123.mongodb.net/dexto?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=Cluster0"

# JWT Secret (CHANGE THIS in production - use a strong random string)
# Generate one: openssl rand -base64 64
JWT_SECRET="change-this-to-a-secure-random-key-in-production-min-32-chars"

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV="development"

# Socket.io Service Port (for mini-service)
SOCKET_PORT=3003

# ============================================
# MONGODB ATLAS SETUP (FREE)
# ============================================
# 1. Go to: https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas/register
# 2. Create a FREE account
# 3. Build a Database → Choose M0 (Free tier)
# 4. Database Access → Add New User:
#    - Username: dexto_admin
#    - Password: (choose a strong password)
# 5. Network Access → Add IP Address → Allow Access From Anywhere (0.0.0.0/0)
# 6. Database → Connect → Drivers → Node.js
# 7. Copy the connection string and replace <password> above
# 8. Add /dexto before the ? in the URL to specify the database name

# ============================================
# VERCEL DEPLOYMENT
# ============================================
# 1. Push your code to GitHub
# 2. Go to: https://vercel.com → New Project → Import your repo
# 3. Add Environment Variables:
#    - DATABASE_URL = (your MongoDB Atlas connection string)
#    - JWT_SECRET = (your strong random secret)
#    - NODE_ENV = production
# 4. Deploy!

# ============================================
# PRODUCTION CHECKLIST
# ============================================
# 1. Change JWT_SECRET to a strong random string
# 2. Use MongoDB Atlas (free tier is enough to start)
# 3. Set NODE_ENV=production
# 4. Change default admin credentials (login → Settings → Admin Account)
# 5. Configure proper USDT wallet addresses for each network
# 6. Enable HTTPS (automatic on Vercel)
